Setting up a Raspberry Pi for a Kubernetes Cluster
=======

1. Install on the raspberrypi the raspbian version: Raspbian Stretch Lite ([from here](https://www.raspberrypi.org/downloads/raspbian/)).
2. After burn the SO to the SD card, create a file called ssh on the /boot directory.
3. Connect the raspberrypi to the local network.
4. Access the raspberrypi using ssh:
  `ssh pi@raspberrypi.local`
5. 
